name: Fresh Strawberry Granita
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ripe strawberries, hulled and halved'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon juice (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'balsamic vinegar (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tiny pinch', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Rinse strawberries with cold water, then drain.. Place berries into a blender with water, sugar, lemon juice, balsamic vinegar, and salt. Pulse several times to get the mixture moving, then blend until smooth, about 1 minute. Pour into a large baking dish; the mixture should only be about 3/8 inch deep in the dish.. Place the uncovered dish into the freezer until the mixture barely begins to freeze around the edges, about 45 minutes, it will still be slushy in the center.. Close the freezer and continue to chill until granita is nearly frozen, 30 to 40 more minutes. Mix lightly again with a fork as before, scraping the crystals loose. name: Gingerbread Biscotti
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'molasses'}, {'quantity': '2 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole wheat flour'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground cloves'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}
steps: Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease a cookie sheet.. Combine sugar, eggs, oil, and molasses in a large bowl. Combine all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, ground ginger, baking powder, ground cinnamon, ground cloves, and ground nutmeg in a separate bowl; stir into sugar mixture until a stiff dough forms.. Divide dough in half; shape each into a roll the length of the cookie sheet. Place rolls on the prepared cookie sheet; pat down to flatten dough until 1/2-inch thick.. Bake in the preheated oven for 25 minutes. Remove from oven; set aside to cool.. When cool enough to touch, cut into 1/2-inch thick diagonal slices.. Place sliced biscotti on cookie sheet; bake until toasted and crispy, 5 to 7 minutes on each side.

name: Fish Sinigang (Tilapia) - Filipino Sour Broth Dish
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'tilapia fillets, cut into chunks'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small head', 'name': 'bok choy, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'tomatoes, cut into chunks'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'thinly sliced daikon radish'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'tamarind paste'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'dried red chile peppers (Optional)'}
steps: In a medium pot, combine the tilapia, bok choy, tomatoes and radish. Stir together the tamarind paste and water; pour into the pot. Toss in the chili peppers if using. Bring to a boil, and cook for 5 minutes, or just until the fish is cooked through. Even frozen fish will cook in less than 10 minutes. Do not over cook or else the fish will fall apart. Ladle into bowls to serve.

name: Broccoli Soup
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, peeled and chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(10 ounce) packages', 'name': 'chopped frozen broccoli, thawed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'potato, peeled and chopped'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}
steps: Heat olive oil in a large saucepan, and sauté onion and garlic until tender. Mix in broccoli, potato, and chicken broth. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer 15 minutes, until vegetables are tender.. With a hand mixer or in a blender, puree the mixture until smooth. Return to the saucepan, and reheat. Season with nutmeg, salt, and pepper.

name: Roasted Eggplant and Mushrooms
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'medium eggplant, peeled and cubed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'zucchini, cubed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'yellow onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'mushrooms, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'tomato paste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried basil'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}
steps: Preheat oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C).. Place eggplant, zucchini, onion and mushrooms in a 2 quart casserole dish. In a small bowl combine the tomato paste with the water, and stir in garlic, basil, salt and pepper. Pour over the vegetables and mix well.. Bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes, or until eggplant is tender, stirring occasionally. Add water as necessary if vegetables begin to stick; however, vegetables should be fairly dry, with slightly browned edges.

Roasted Green Beans and Baby Red Potatoes
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'olive oil cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'baby red potatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'fresh green beans, trimmed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried parsley'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Spray a rimmed baking sheet with cooking spray.. Cut potatoes in half if they are golf-ball-sized or larger. Lay potatoes and green beans in a single layer on the prepared baking sheet and spray with cooking spray. Sprinkle salt, garlic powder, pepper, and parsley on top.. Bake in the preheated oven until potatoes are tender, 25 to 30 minutes.
